Class Positionn

java.lang.Object
com.example.projectfx.ecosystem.Positionn
public class Positionn extends Object
Represents a position in a 2D space, defined by x and y coordinates. This class provides functionality to handle random position generation, distance calculation, and position movement, while ensuring no overlap with existing positions within a specified minimum distance.

      public Positionn(int rangeMinX, int rangeMaxX, int rangeMinY, int rangeMaxY, List<Positionn> existingPositions, int minDistance)
      Constructs a random position within specified ranges for x and y coordinates, ensuring that the position does not overlap with any existing positions and maintains a minimum distance from others.
      Parameters:
      rangeMinX - the minimum possible x-coordinate value.
      rangeMaxX - the maximum possible x-coordinate value.
      rangeMinY - the minimum possible y-coordinate value.
      rangeMaxY - the maximum possible y-coordinate value.
      existingPositions - the list of existing positions to check for overlap.
      minDistance - the minimum allowed distance between the new position and existing ones.
